Yea , gentlemen , are you here before us ? How is he now ?
Faith , the same man still : the tavern bitch has bit him i' th '
head .
We shall have the better sport with him ; peace ! And how cheers
Master Dampit now ?
Oh , my bosom Sir Lancelot , how cheer I ! Thy presence is restorative .
But I hear a great complaint of you , Master Dampit , among gallants .
I am glad of that , i'faith ; prithee , what ?
They say you are waxed proud a'late , and if a friend visit you
in the afternoon , you 'll scarce know him .
Fie , fie ! Proud ? I cannot remember any such thing ; sure I was
drunk then .
Think you so , sir ?
There 'twas , i'faith , nothing but the pride of the sack , and so
certify 'em . Fetch sack , sirrah !
A vengeance sack you once !
Why , Master Dampit , if you hold on as you begin , and lie a little
longer , you need not take care how to dispose your wealth ; you 'll
